condary:&nbsp;7|Adult:&nbsp;1}}\n| budget = {{CAD|link=yes}}278 million<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hwcdsb.ca/budgetandfinancial/|title=Budget and Financial Statements|website=Hamilton-Wentworth Catholic District School Board|language=en|access-date=2019-08-12}}</ref> (2019)\n| accreditations = \n| faculty = \n| teachers = \n| staff = \n| ratio = \n| conference = Hamilton-Wentworth Catholic Athletic Association (HWCAA)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hwcdsb.ca/participate/hwcaaconstitution/|title=Athletic Association Constitution & Forms|website=Hamilton-Wentworth Catholic District School Board|language=en|access-date=2019-08-12|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190410163529/https://www.hwcdsb.ca/participate/hwcaaconstitution/|archivedate=April 10, 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n| colours = [[Blue]] and [[Orange (colour)|Orange]] {{color box|blue}}{{color box|orange}}\n| schedule = [[Monday to Friday]]; except [[holiday|holidays]]\n| website = {{URL|www.hwcdsb.ca}}\n| module = {{Location map|Canada Ontario|embed=yes|float=center|caption=Location of board office|alt=Map of Ontario with pin showing location of board office|label=Board office|lat_deg=43.26303|lon_deg=-79.87055}}\n}}\n\nThe '''Hamilton-Wentworth Catholic District School Board''' is the [[Catholic school#Canada|Catholic]] [[Board of education|school board]] for the city of [[Hamilton, Ontario|Hamilton]], [[Ontario]] which includes the former [[Wentworth County, Ontario|Wentworth County]]. It currently operates 54 schools: 46 elementary, 7 secondary and 1 adult school.\n\n== History ==\nThe '''Hamilton Separate School Board''' (HSSB) was established in 1855 and the seven other boards were formed for the next 114 years in Wentworth County. In 1969, the boards became known as the '''Hamilton-Wentworth Roman Catholic Separate School Board''' (HWRCSSB).<ref name=History>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hwcdsb.ca/aboutus/history/|title=History|website=www.hwcdsb.ca|language=en|access-date=2019-08-12}}</ref>\n\nFollowing the Ontario government's passage of the ''Fewer School Boards Act'' of 1997, the HWRCSSB became the ''English-language Separate District School Board No. 47'' in 1998 and was renamed to the ''Hamilton-Wentworth Catholic District School Board'' in 1999. French language schools operated by its francophone unit, the ''Le conseil des \u00e9coles s\u00e9par\u00e9es catholiques romaines de Hamilton-Wentworth'' became part of ''French-language Separate District School Board No. 58'', which later became the [[Conseil scolaire catholique MonAvenir|Conseil scolaire de district catholique Centre-Sud]].<ref name=History /> \n\n== Schools ==\n=== Adult Schools/Continuing Education Centres ===\n{{div col|colwidth=25em}}\n* St. Charles\n{{div col end}}\n\n=== Secondary Schools ===\n{{div col|colwidth=25em}}\n* [[Bishop Ryan Catholic Secondary School|Bishop Ryan]]\n* [[Bishop Tonnos Catholic Secondary School|Bishop Tonnos]]\n* [[Cardinal Newman Secondary School|Cardinal Newman]]\n* [[Cathedral High School (Hamilton, Ontario)|Cathedral]]\n* [[St. Jean de Br\u00e9beuf Catholic Secondary School|St. Jean de Br\u00e9beuf]]\n* [[St. Mary Catholic Secondary School (Hamilton, Ontario)|St. Mary]]\n* [[St. Thomas More Catholic Secondary School|St. Thomas More]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n=== Elementary Schools ===\n{{div col|colwidth=25em}}\n* Annunciation of Our Lord\n* Blessed Sacrament\n* Canadian Martyrs\n* Corpus Christi\n* Guardian Angels\n* Holy Name of Jesus\n* Holy Name of Mary\n* Immaculate Conception\n* Immaculate Heart of Mary\n* Our Lady of Lourdes\n* Our Lady of Mount Carmel\n* Our Lady of Peace\n* Our Lady of the Assumption\n* Regina Mundi\n* Sacred Heart of Jesus\n* St. Agnes\n* St. Ann (Ancaster)\n* St. Ann (Hamilton)\n* St. Anthony Daniel\n* St. Augustine\n* St. Bernadette\n* St. Brigid\n* St. Clare of Assisi\n* St. David\n* St. Eugene\n* St. Francis Xavier\n* St. Gabriel\n* St. James the Apostle\n* St. Joachim\n* St. John Paul II\n* St. John the Baptist\n* St. Joseph\n* St. Kateri Tekakwitha\n* St. Lawrence\n* St. Luke\n* St. Margaret Mary\n* St. Marguerite d'Youville\n* St. Mark\n* St. Martin of Tours\n* St. Matthew\n* St. Michael\n* St. Patrick\n* St. Paul\n* St. Teresa of Avila\n* St. Teresa of Calcutta\n* St. Th\u00e9r\u00e8se of Lisieux\n* St. Thomas the Apostle\n* St. Vincent de Paul\n* Sts. Peter and Paul\n{{div col end}}'''The following Schools in Hamilton-Wentworth Catholic District School Board that offers French Immersion:'''\n\n# St. Clare of Assisi Catholic Elementary [https://stcl.hwcdsb.ca/ School]\n# St. Vincent de Paul Catholic Elementary [https://stvp.hwcdsb.ca/ School]\n# St. Joseph Catholic Elementary [https://stjs.hwcdsb.ca/ School]\n# St. Eugene Catholic Elementary [https://steu.hwcdsb.ca/ School]\n# Sts. Peter & Paul Catholic Elementary [https://stpp.hwcdsb.ca/ School]\n\n\n'''Benefits of French Immersion Schools:'''\n\nFrench immersion programs are essential and functional for students' everyday life in Canada. Learning French is like any other task, it can be difficult at first, but eventually, it becomes subconscious. The earlier the student can be exposed to it, the easier it will be grasped. Students that are in French Immersion schools complete the same curriculum subjects as other schools but have the advantage of learning a new language.\n\nThe French Immersion program was designed to take benefit of children's capacity to learn freely and smoothly. Also, take advantage of their communicative competence and open perspectives on language and society. Therefore, learning French becomes unconscious, and there is a heavy focus on understanding before pronouncing.\n\n\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Hamilton-Wentworth District School Board]]\n* [[:Category:High schools in Hamilton, Ontario|List of High Schools in Hamilton]]\n* [[List of school districts in Ontario]]\n* [[List of high schools in Ontario]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website}}\n* {{URL|https://www.hwcdsb.ca/board/policies/|Policies, Protocols and By-Laws}}\n* {{URL|https://www.hwcdsb.ca/board/meetingsminutes/|Public Meetings and Minutes}}\n\n{{Hamilton}}\n\n[[Category:Education in Hamilton, Ontario]]\n[[Category:Roman Catholic school districts in Ontario]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Catholic school board}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=November 2018}}\n{{Use Canadian English|date=November 2018}}\n{{Infobox school district\n| name = Hamilton-Wentworth Catholic District School Board\n| logo = Hamilton-Wentworth CDSB logo.jpg\n| logo_alt = Hamilton-Wentworth Catholic District School Board logo\n| logo_caption = Hamilton-Wentworth Catholic District School Board logo\n| address = 90 Mulberry Street\n| city = [[Hamilton, Ontario|Hamilton]]\n| province = [[Ontario]]\n| postalcode = [[Postal codes in Canada|L8R 2C8]]\n| country = Canada\n| coordinates = {{coord|43.26303|N|79.87055|W|type:edu_region:CA-ON|display=inline,title}}\n| type = [[Board of education|School Board]]\n| motto = Believing, Achieving, Serving\n| grades = [[Kindergarten|K]]\u2013[[Twelfth grade|{{Ordinal|12|sup=yes}}]]\n| established = {{Unbulleted list|{{Start date and age|1855}}|1969 (amalgamation)|1998 (present form)}}\n| chair_of_the_board = Patrick J. Daly\n| director_of_education = David Hansen<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hwcdsb.ca/90622--New-Director-of-Education-to-head-up-HWCDSB|title=New Director of Education to head up HWCDSB|website=Hamilton-Wentworth Catholic District School Board|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181123112151/https://www.hwcdsb.ca/90622--New-Director-of-Education-to-head-up-HWCDSB|archive-date=November 23, 2018|url-status=dead|access-date=2018-11-22}}</ref>\n| governing_agency = [[Ministry of Education (Ontario)|Ministry of Education]]\n| schools = {{Unbulleted list|Elementary:&nbsp;46<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hwcdsb.ca/scripts/custom/printableschoollist/|title=Printable School List|date=2018|website=Hamilton-Wentworth Catholic District School Board|forma