atholic Separate School Board''' (HWRCSSB).<ref name=History>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hwcdsb.ca/aboutus/history/|title=History|website=www.hwcdsb.ca|language=en|access-date=2019-08-12}}</ref>\n\nFollowing the Ontario government's passage of the ''Fewer School Boards Act'' of 1997, the HWRCSSB became the ''English-language Separate District School Board No. 47'' in 1998 and was renamed to the ''Hamilton-Wentworth Catholic District School Board'' in 1999. French language schools operated by its francophone unit, the ''Le conseil des \u00e9coles s\u00e9par\u00e9es catholiques romaines de Hamilton-Wentworth'' became part of ''French-language Separate District School Board No. 58'', which later became the [[Conseil scolaire catholique MonAvenir|Conseil scolaire de district catholique Centre-Sud]].<ref name=History /> \n\n== Schools ==\n=== Adult Schools/Continuing Education Centres ===\n{{div col|colwidth=25em}}\n* St. Charles\n{{div col end}}\n\n=== Secondary Schools ===\n{{div col|colwidth=25em}}\n* [[Bishop Ryan Catholic Secondary School|Bishop Ryan]]\n* [[Bishop Tonnos Catholic Secondary School|Bishop Tonnos]]\n* [[Cardinal Newman Secondary School|Cardinal Newman]]\n* [[Cathedral High School (Hamilton, Ontario)|Cathedral]]\n* [[St. Jean de Br\u00e9beuf Catholic Secondary School|St. Jean de Br\u00e9beuf]]\n* [[St. Mary Catholic Secondary School (Hamilton, Ontario)|St. Mary]]\n* [[St. Thomas More Catholic Secondary School|St. Thomas More]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n=== Elementary Schools ===\n{{div col|colwidth=25em}}\n* Annunciation of Our Lord\n* Blessed Sacrament\n* Canadian Martyrs\n* Corpus Christi\n* Guardian Angels\n* Holy Name of Jesus\n* Holy Name of Mary\n* Immaculate Conception\n* Immaculate Heart of Mary\n* Our Lady of Lourdes\n* Our Lady of Mount Carmel\n* Our Lady of Peace\n* Our Lady of the Assumption\n* Regina Mundi\n* Sacred Heart of Jesus\n* St. Agnes\n* St. Ann (Ancaster)\n* St. Ann (Hamilton)\n* St. Anthony Daniel\n* St. Augustine\n* St. Bernadette\n* St. Brigid\n* St. Clare of Assisi\n* St. David\n* St. Eugene\n* St. Francis Xavier\n* St. Gabriel\n* St. James the Apostle\n* St. Joachim\n* St. John Paul II\n* St. John the Baptist\n* St. Joseph\n* St. Kateri Tekakwitha\n* St. Lawrence\n* St. Luke\n* St. Margaret Mary\n* St. Marguerite d'Youville\n* St. Mark\n* St. Martin of Tours\n* St. Matthew\n* St. Michael\n* St. Patrick\n* St. Paul\n* St. Teresa of Avila\n* St. Teresa of Calcutta\n* St. Th\u00e9r\u00e8se of Lisieux\n* St. Thomas the Apostle\n* St. Vincent de Paul\n* Sts. Peter and Paul\n{{div col end}}'''The following Schools in Hamilton-Wentworth Catholic District School Board that offers French Immersion:'''\n\n# St. Clare of Assisi Catholic Elementary [https://stcl.hwcdsb.ca/ School]\n# St. Vincent de Paul Catholic Elementary [https://stvp.hwcdsb.ca/ School]\n# St. Joseph Catholic Elementary [https://stjs.hwcdsb.ca/ School]\n# St. Eugene Catholic Elementary [https://steu.hwcdsb.ca/ School]\n# Sts. Peter & Paul Catholic Elementary [https://stpp.hwcdsb.ca/ School]\n\n\n'''Benefits of French Immersion Schools:'''\n\nClassroom communication of French in bilingual education programs is meaningful and authentic for students. Learning French becomes subconscious and creates a strong focus on understanding before speaking. Most students that enrol in French Immersion programs are not experts in French and often lack experience. Students in French immersion programs complete the same curriculum as students in non-immersion programs. \n\nThe French immersion was designed to: (a) capitalize on children's ability to learn language naturally and effortlessly; (b) take advantage of their social ability and open attitudes to language and culture; (c) reflect on the building blocks of language by emphasizing the use of languages for communication and (d) not stopping the children from participating in native language development, academic achievement or general cognitive development.<ref>{{Citation|title=French immersion|date=2020-03-14|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=French_immersion&oldid=945509120|work=Wikipedia|language=en|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref>\n\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Hamilton-Wentworth District School Board]]\n* [[:Category:High schools in Hamilton, Ontario|List of High Schools in Hamilton]]\n* [[List of school districts in Ontario]]\n* [[List of high schools in Ontario]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website}}\n* {{URL|https://www.hwcdsb.ca/board/policies/|Policies, Protocols and By-Laws}}\n* {{URL|https://www.hwcdsb.ca/board/meetingsminutes/|Public Meetings and Minutes}}\n\n{{Hamilton}}\n\n[[Category:Education in Hamilton, Ontario]]\n[[Category:Roman Catholic school districts in Ontario]]\n", "name_user": "Ellsmers", "label": "safe", "comment": "changed the paragraph of the Benefits of French Immersion Schools.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hamilton-Wentworth_Catholic_District_School_Board"}
