{"title_page": "Kristel Werckx", "text_new": "{{short description|Belgian cyclist}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox cyclist\n| name           = Kristel Werckx\n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| fullname       = Kristel Werckx\n| nickname       = \n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1969|12|16|df=yes}}\n| birth_place    = [[Heusden-Zolder]], [[Belgium]]\n| death_date     = \n| death_place    = \n| height         = \n| weight         = \n| discipline     = \n| role           = Rider\n| ridertype      = \n| amateuryears1  = \n| amateurteam1   = \n| proyears1      = \n| proteam1       = \n| majorwins      = \n| medaltemplates = \n| show-medals    = \n| updated        = \n}}\n'''Kristel Werckx''' (born 16 December 1969) is a former Belgian [[bicycle racing|racing cyclist]]. She won the [[Belgian National Road Race Championships|Belgian national road race title]] in 1991 and 1993.<ref name=\"CyclingArchives\">{{cite web |url=http://www.cyclingarchives.com/coureurfiche.php?coureurid=19075 |title=Kristel Werckx |accessdate=3 May 2014 |work=Cycling Archives}}</ref> She also competed at the [[1988 Summer Olympics|1988]] and [[1992 Summer Olympics]].<ref name=\"SportsRef\">{{cite web |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/we/kristel-werckx-1.html |title=Kristel Werckx |accessdate=3 May 2014 |work=Sports Reference}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{cycling archives|19075}}\n\n{{Belgian National Road Race Championships (women) |state=collapsed}}\n{{Belgian National Time Trial Champion \u2013 Women's Elite |state=collapsed}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Werckx, Kristel}}\n[[Category:1969 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Belgian female cyclists]]\n[[Category:People from Heusden-Zolder]]\n[[Category:Olympic cyclists of Belgium]]\n[[Category:Cyclists at the 1988 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Cyclists at the 1992 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Limburg (Belgium)]]\n{{Belgium-cycling-bio-1960s-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Belgian cyclist}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2014}}\n{{Infobox cyclist\n| name           = Kristel Werckx\n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| fullname       = Kristel Werckx\n| nickname       = \n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1969|12|16|df=yes}}\n| birth_place    = [[Heusden-Zolder]], [[Belgium]]\n| death_date     = \n| death_place    = \n| height         = \n| weight         = \n| discipline     = \n| role           = Rider\n| ridertype      = \n| amateuryears1  = \n| amateurteam1   = \n| proyears1      = \n| proteam1       = \n| majorwins      = \n| medaltemplates = \n| show-medals    = \n| updated        = \n}}\n'''Kristel Werckx''' (born 16 December 1969) is a former Belgian [[bicycle racing|racing cyclist]]. She won the [[Belgian National Road Race Championships|Belgian national road race title]] in 1991 and 1993.<ref name=\"CyclingArchives\">{{cite web |url=http://www.cyclingarchives.com/coureurfiche.php?coureurid=19075 |title=Kristel Werckx |accessdate=3 May 2014 |work=Cycling Archives}}</ref> She also competed at the [[1988 Summer Olympics|1988]] and [[1992 Summer Olympics]].<ref name=\"SportsRef\">{{cite web |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/we/kristel-werckx-1.html |title=Kristel Werckx |accessdate=3 May 2014 |work=Sports Reference}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{cycling archives|19075}}\n\n{{Belgian National Road Race Championships (women) |state=collapsed}}\n{{Belgian National Time Trial Champion \u2013 Women's Elite |state=collapsed}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Werckx, Kristel}}\n[[Category:1969 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Belgian female cyclists]]\n[[Category:People from Heusden-Zolder]]\n[[Category:Olympic cyclists of Belgium]]\n[[Category:Cyclists at the 1988 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Cyclists at the 1992 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Limburg (Belgium)]]