{"title_page": "Karen Steurs", "text_new": "{{short description|Belgian cyclist}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox cyclist\n| name           = Karen Steurs\n| image          =\n| caption        =\n| fullname       = Karen Steurs\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1979|8|27|df=yes}}\n| birth_place    = [[Schoten]], [[Belgium]]\n| death_date     =\n| death_place    =\n| height         =\n| weight         =\n| discipline     =\n| role           = Rider\n| ridertype      =\n| amateuryears1  =\n| amateurteam1   =\n| proyears1      =\n| proteam1       =\n| majorwins      =\n| medaltemplates =\n| show-medals    =\n| updated        =\n}}\n'''Karen Steurs''' (born 27 August 1979) is a former Belgian [[bicycle racing|racing cyclist]]. She finished second place in the [[Belgian National Road Race Championships]] in 2006.<ref name=\"CyclingArchives\">{{cite web |url=http://www.cyclingarchives.com/coureurfiche.php?coureurid=28483 |title=Karen Steurs |accessdate=4 May 2014 |work=Cycling Archives}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{cycling archives|28483}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Steurs, Karen}}\n[[Category:1979 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Belgian female cyclists]]\n[[Category:People from Schoten]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Antwerp (province)]]\n{{Belgium-cycling-bio-1970s-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Belgian cyclist}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2014}}\n{{Infobox cyclist\n| name           = Karen Steurs\n| image          =\n| caption        =\n| fullname       = Karen Steurs\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1979|8|27|df=yes}}\n| birth_place    = [[Schoten]], [[Belgium]]\n| death_date     =\n| death_place    =\n| height         =\n| weight         =\n| discipline     =\n| role           = Rider\n| ridertype      =\n| amateuryears1  =\n| amateurteam1   =\n| proyears1      =\n| proteam1       =\n| majorwins      =\n| medaltemplates =\n| show-medals    =\n| updated        =